1. Technical Requirements (Vector & Quality)
Scalability: The logo must look equally sharp on a business card (10 mm) and on a billboard (5 meters). Loss of detail when scaled down significantly is unacceptable.

Vector Format: Source files must be provided in .AI (Adobe Illustrator), .EPS, and .SVG formats. Raster .PNG is only an addition.

Resolution: For raster versions (.PNG, .JPG), the resolution must be at least 300 DPI at the actual size of use.

2. Color Requirements
Monochrome Version: A black-and-white version of the logo (100% Black and/or White on transparent) is mandatory. The logo must work without color.

Color Models: Files must be provided in CMYK (for print) and RGB (for screens).

Number of Colors: It is recommended to use no more than 3 main colors (unless related to the brand's rainbow identity).

Contrast: The logo must be contrasting on white, black, and the brand's branded background.

3. Composition Requirements
Legibility: Text (if any) must not read as an abstract pattern. Excessive deformation of the font (narrowing, stretching without preserving proportions) is prohibited.

Geometric Purity: All lines must be visually precise (using grids, circles, the golden ratio). No "wobbling" of curves.

Clear Space (Safety Zone): There must be empty space around the logo equal to the height of the letter "X" or the diameter of the central element. No text or graphics may invade this zone.

4. Adaptability (Variations)
Vertical and Horizontal Layout: Two layout arrangements must be available (e.g., "Icon + text on the right" and "Icon above text").

Favicon: Adaptation of the logo for a website icon (16x16, 32x32, 64x64 pixels) without loss of meaning. This may sometimes require creating a simplified version of the mark without text.

Reversed Version: A logo that can be placed over photographs (must have a stroke, background plate, or be white/black).

5. Legal Requirements
Uniqueness: The logo must not resemble famous logos (trademark database checks are at the client's discretion, but the requirement for the designer is not to use stock icons as a base).

Printing Technology Feasibility: Lines that are too thin (less than 0.2 pt at 1:1 scale for a business card) and too small negative spaces that could fill with ink during offset printing are prohibited.

6. Aesthetics & Meaning
Timelessness: The logo should look relevant for at least 5-10 years (avoid trends like acidic neon gradients, glitch effects, or complex gradients unless they are the brand's specific feature).

Associativity: The form should intuitively hint at the field of activity (circle/softness for massage, angles/chiseled fonts for construction), or be abstract but memorable.

Project Delivery Checklist:
Main color version (horizontal/vertical).

Monochrome black version.

Monochrome white version.

Logo on a complex background (photo/texture).

Logo at minimum size (down to 20 pixels).

All fonts (in a Fonts folder) and color palette.
